# Layout Width

Project standard **modal** width: **`max-w-4xl`** (56rem) via `.app-modal` / `.app-width`.

## Use `max-w-4xl` for

- Modals only — `components/common/Modal.jsx` (`.app-modal` includes it)
- Any new dialog or overlay panel

## Do NOT apply to

- **Main page content** — stays full width within `.shell-content` (`max-w-7xl`)
- **Page cards** (`.shell-page-card`) — no max-width; fill the content area

## Exceptions

- **Login form** — compact at `max-w-md`
- **Toasts** — `max-w-sm`

## New modals

Reuse `Modal` from `components/common/Modal.jsx`:

```jsx
<Modal title="Title" onClose={close} ariaLabelledBy="modal-title-id">
  {/* content */}
</Modal>
```

Do not introduce alternate max-widths for modals unless the user explicitly requests it.
